reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2024
reviews.reviewText: We ordered this truck for my son for Christmas in December. Here we are in February and he plays with this daily. This truck has many cool features that he loves to play with like the ramp where the cars go down. Everything is durable and still in working order. I love the fact that it is able to expand to play with and then compact back down to be played with as a regular truck!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Fun Toy, Easy Storage
reviews.reviewText: I got this toy for my 4 year old. He loves racing cars. The propelling mechanism is really neat and it's easy to fold up and store. It's meant for children who are a little more careful with toys. My son leaned on it and ended up snapping some of the supporting stands. Not much putting together in the front end. The toy is really convenient, it's easy to take out of the box and go right to playing.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Small and not sturdy
reviews.reviewText: I brought this for my grandson as he loves any type of vehicle. It appeared sturdy, but the small pieces that hold the vehicle up so you can ride the cars is extremely flimsy. The comparison of the child on the photo to the vehicle is extremely exaggerated. The vehicle is small. Not really made for a child that really wants to play with it. He still plays with it but I have to put something under the extension piece as it no longer stays up on the side holders. Would I recommend this...... Not really. Only if your child is an extremely calm and super careful kid. Good luck....
